---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { externalLinks, repoUrls } from '../../config';
---

<Layout title="Annex A — Terms of Reference">
  <p class="text-sm text-ink-subtle"><a href="/specification">← Specification</a></p>
  <h1 class="text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-2">Annex A — Terms of Reference</h1>
  <p class="text-sm text-ink-subtle mb-8">
    The Terms of Reference for the ISO 24229 Registration Authority, per
    Annex A of the
    <a href={externalLinks.iso24229Standard} class="underline">published standard</a>.
  </p>

  <section id="ra" class="border-t border-line py-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">A.1 Registration authority (ISO 24229/RA)</h2>
    <p>
      ISO has designated a Registration Authority to register conversion
      system codes and conversion system authority identifiers. The official
      listing of the RA is at
      <a href="https://www.iso.org/mara" class="underline">iso.org/mara</a>.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-medium mt-6 mb-2">Functions of the RA</h3>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-ink-muted">
      <li>Add and eliminate entries per the rules in the standard.</li>
      <li>Advise users and ISO member bodies on the application of the register.</li>
      <li>Update and disseminate the register.</li>
      <li>Maintain a reference list of register entries.</li>
      <li>Publish changes and the history of changes for traceability.</li>
      <li>Administer the reservation of code elements.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-medium mt-6 mb-2">Data the RA provides per code</h3>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-ink-muted">
      <li>the conversion system code</li>
      <li>the name of the conversion system and its authority</li>
      <li>the source language and script of the conversion system</li>
      <li>the target language and script of the conversion system</li>
      <li>the source bibliographic reference</li>
      <li>method identifier of the conversion system</li>
      <li>status of the conversion system code</li>
      <li>relationship with other conversion systems</li>
      <li>any associated remarks</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink-subtle">
      Changes become effective immediately upon publication by the RA.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="ag" class="border-t border-line py-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">A.2 Advisory group (ISO 24229/AG)</h2>
    <p>
      To ensure transparency and that the RA operates per the standard, the RA
      appoints an Advisory Group of <strong>at least 4 and up to 12 members</strong>.
      The AG consists of experts in script or other conversions, information
      technologies, and library management. It includes a representative of
      ISO/TC 46 and may include representatives of organizations interested
      in using the codes.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-medium mt-6 mb-2">Decision-making</h3>
    <p>
      As a rule, the AG makes decisions <strong>by consensus</strong>.
      If a vote is needed, the decision is approved when
      <strong>more than two-thirds of members vote for it</strong>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="operations-authorities" class="border-t border-line py-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">A.3 Operations on conversion system authorities</h2>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-medium mt-2 mb-2">Registration of a new authority</h3>
    <p>
      Additions are made upon request from a member of the AG. An authority
      is eligible if it meets the requirements in §5 of the standard
      (competence in managing conversion systems; at least one eligible
      system). The proposer provides justification; the AG decides.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-medium mt-4 mb-2">Marking an authority inactive</h3>
    <p>
      The AG may mark an authority inactive if it ceases to exist or no
      longer wishes to register systems. The AG determines what information
      remains, on the basis of practicality and continuity of usage.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-medium mt-4 mb-2">Modifications to identifiers</h3>
    <p>
      Modifications are made upon request from an AG member or the authority
      itself. Significant name changes may result in a new identifier; the
      previously assigned identifier is reserved for backwards compatibility.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-medium mt-4 mb-2">Varia authorities</h3>
    <p>
      The "<em>Varia systems</em>" authority is assigned the identifier
      <code>Var</code>. The AG manages systems that need representation but
      have no clear extant authority. Example: the Wade-Giles Chinese
      transcription is encoded as <code>Var:zho-Hani:Latn:WG-1912</code>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="operations-systems" class="border-t border-line py-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">A.4 Operations on written language conversion systems</h2>
    <p>
      Alterations to a registered entry are made only upon request from an
      AG member or the managing authority. Significant name changes may
      require a new code element; stability of the code list is otherwise
      preserved.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="reservation" class="border-t border-line py-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">A.5 Reservation of code elements</h2>
    <p>
      Code elements may be reserved:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mt-2">
      <li>for a limited period, when the reservation results from deprecation or alteration;</li>
      <li>for an indeterminate period, when the reservation results from international law or exceptional requests.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mt-3">
      Altered or deleted codes should not be reallocated indefinitely. The
      RA maintains a list of reserved code elements.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="advice" class="border-t border-line py-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">A.6 Advice regarding use</h2>
    <p>
      The AG is available for consultation and assistance on the use of
      codes for conversion system authorities and written language
      conversion systems.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="this-site" class="border-t border-line py-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">About this register deployment</h2>
    <p>
      This website is the operational deployment of the ISO 24229 register,
      maintained at <a href={repoUrls.register} class="underline">{repoUrls.register}</a>.
      The Registration Authority is
      <a href={externalLinks.calconnect} class="underline">CalConnect</a>,
      designated by ISO/TC 46/WG 3. The register is operated by
      <a href={externalLinks.ribose} class="underline">Ribose</a>, a CalConnect member.
      We have adopted a bimonthly meeting cadence (operational choice, not
      mandated by the standard) and require each authority to designate two
      authorised persons (also an operational choice for accountability).
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout>
